

=Bio=

"Dr Gregor Kaiser is a social scientist and biologist, working on iussues like agriculture, biopiracy, intellectual property rights, seed laws and commons. He runs a small family owned forest enterprice in Sauerland Region, 100km North-East of Cologne. His thinking on IPR issues led to a fundamental questioning of the commercial seed breeding and financing and he asks for alternatives based on local expiriences and social interaction."


=Publications=

He is Co-author of the paper: Open Source for Seeds (2012, only German yet). 


